snippet.textDisplay: Every moment on the field at Anfield makes me a proud Liverpool fan. What a night!!! A lot of highpoints in this historical match. Youngest ever  Liverpool team, Curtis Jones youngest Liverpool captain ever, Legendary James Milner forfeiting his holiday for the team to ensure victory and impressive team spirit, sportsmanship and leadership qualities demonstrated by Coash Critshley, the coach's public attestation of Milners' contributions to the team's success. Critshley has proven to Klopp and Liverpool fans all over the world in the front of the Kop that he's an able representative by allstandards, doing what many believed is impossible and therefore deserves a Liverpool's meritorious award. The boys gave a good account of themselves to prove to anyone who cares to listen that what the men can do the boys can also do. They have kept the trebles' hope alive despite the fact that no one including my goodself gave them a chance and this will not be forgotten so soon. I'm so proud of the boys. Thank you for taking us to the next round boys,  YNWA

Critshley has proven to Klopp and Liverpool fans all over the world in the front of the Kop that he's an able representative by allstandards, doing what many believed is impossible and therefore deserves a Liverpool's meritorious award.
